## Project Motivation

Most memory games offer static levels where every player follows exactly the same progression regardless of their individual abilities.

The objective of Memory was to create a system capable of analysing user behaviour and automatically adapting future training sessions, providing a more personalized and effective cognitive training experience.

---

## Adaptive Cognitive Engine

The application continuously analyses:

- completion time,
- player effectiveness,
- board configuration,
- previous sessions,
- gameplay strategy,
- mistake frequency,
- player progress.

Based on these factors, the application dynamically adjusts the difficulty level instead of relying on predefined progression.

---

## Player Behaviour Analysis

Instead of treating every incorrect move equally, the system classifies different categories of mistakes:

- Cognitive mistakes
- Associative mistakes
- Spatial mistakes
- Attention mistakes

The application also recognises different playing strategies, reducing false classifications and improving the quality of behavioural analysis.

